==English==

===Etymology===
From Korean [[구결]] / [[口訣]] (gukyeol).

===Proper noun===
'''Kwukyel'''

# One of three early systems for writing Korean with Chinese characters before the invention of the modern [[Hangul]] ([[한글]]) script, resembling the old Japanese [[kanbun]] ([[漢文]]) style. The other two ancient Korean systems were [[Hyangchal]] and [[Itwu]].

===Alternative spellings===
*[[Gukyeol]]

===Characters===
[[丆]], [[乊]], [[厼]], [[壭]], [[罖]], [[卪]], [[朩]], [[亪]], [[仒]]

